Broadway composer and lyricist Stephen Schwartz interviewed; The Big Year reviewed by Alex Horne; 
 
Following a new report from Arts Council England on Internships in the Arts, Martin Bright, founder of New Deal of the Mind, and Richard Mantle, General Director of Opera North, discuss whether theatres and galleries can afford to pay interns in these cash-strapped times. 

John Wilson talks to the artist Hilary Lloyd, one of this year's Turner Prize nominees.

